"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s5",
"title":{
"__html":"Esophagitis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"43a601",
"children":[
"Esophagitis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s5_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a26f09",
"children":[
"Odynophagia is the most common presenting symptom of esophagitis."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"fadf93",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Candida albicans"
]
},
" is the most common infectious cause, followed by ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"cytomegalovirus",
"children":[
"CMV"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"herpes simplex virus",
"children":[
"HSV"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"afd124",
"children":[
"Diagnosis is based on compatible symptoms and oral candidiasis."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c61e03",
"children":[
"Patients with oral candidiasis and odynophagia are treated empirically."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gi_f02"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"97bdbf",
"children":[
"Viral esophagitis is found in immunodeficient or immunosuppressed patients, and ulcerative oropharyngeal lesions are rare."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c22e59",
"children":[
"Pill-induced esophagitis may be caused by tetracyclines, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs",
"children":[
"NSAIDs"
]
},
","
]
},
" potassium chloride, iron, and alendronate. Severe substernal chest pain with swallowing occurs several hours to days after taking the medication."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0a345b",
"children":[
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Young adults with eosinophilic esophagitis (EE) present with severe dysphagia and food impaction. "
]
},
"Other atopic conditions, such as asthma, rhinitis, dermatitis, and seasonal or food allergies, are common."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s5_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f12bd7",
"children":[
"Perform upper endoscopy with biopsy/brushing if empiric therapy for esophagitis is unsuccessful."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d6ab38",
"children":[
"Upper endoscopy in patients with ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"eosinophilic esophagitis",
"children":[
"EE"
]
},
" may show mucosal furrowing, stacked circular rings, white specks, and mucosal friability. Endoscopic biopsies show marked infiltration with eosinophils."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s5_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ab65da",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 30-year-old man has frequent heartburn and recurrent episodes of food impaction."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e77ac0",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose eosinophilic esophagitis; confirm with upper endoscopy and biopsy."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e23880",
"children":[
"The absence of oral ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Candida"
]
},
" lesions does not rule out esophageal candidiasis."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s5_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"43a997",
"children":[
"Address the underlying cause of esophagitis:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f95966",
"children":[
"fluconazole or itraconazole for esophageal candidiasis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7375d3",
"children":[
"acyclovir, famciclovir, or valacyclovir for HSV esophagitis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"875d3b",
"children":[
"ganciclovir or valganciclovir for CMV esophagitis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7b3725",
"children":[
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"proton pump inhibitor",
"children":[
"PPI"
]
},
","
]
},
" swallowed fluticasone, or budesonide for EE"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1f4c33",
"children":[
"supportive care for pill esophagitis"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s5_5",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f0f49c",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 28-year-old man with HIV infection has a 2-month history of odynophagia. On physical examination, oral thrush is present."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5e7a16",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Candida"
]
},
" esophagitis. For treatment, select fluconazole."
]
}
]
}
]
